{
  "stem": "26765.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And of course, George was upset, but we got another cart and started the process over again.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it was a wonderful experience to be free, to have survived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "At the same time, it was very sad because originally-- and I got these figures out of Jacob Presser's book, Originally, there were 2,600 people on that train.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "By the time we left Trobitz, there were 600.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So many people had died on the train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Many people died after the liberation in Trobitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Both George and I became sick with typhus.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The Russians had set up a little hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They did their best to help us, and the best way to help us was to get rid of the lice because it's lice that caused the typhus.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And so they cut my hair, and I screamed and yelled, so they left a couple of inches of hair on my head.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But both George and I did get typhus and that we survived was just phenomenal.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But it was a beautiful time of spring, and it was, again, my 10th birthday.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I stepped outside, and I was getting better from the typhus.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I saw this beautiful cherry tree in bloom and it was just-- it symbolized life and another start, and it was so beautiful.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But like I say, it was a sad time because so many people continued to die.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I went back to Trobitz, to the little town, as soon as communism fell in 1991.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And I was so gratified because there was a Jewish cemetery.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Now not all of the Jews who died there are buried in the cemetery, but many of them are.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And the people of Trobitz, especially the children, have maintained that cemetery so beautifully with flowers and shrubs.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
